Wash and dry produce.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @honey{2%teaspoon}, @miso sauce concentrate{1%unit}, 
@soy sauce{2%tablespoon}, @Szechuan paste{2%tablespoon}, half the 
@rice wine vinegar{5%teaspoon}, 2 cups water, and 1⁄4 tsp 
@sugar{1/4%tsp} (all the vinegar, 3 3⁄4 cups water, and 1⁄2 tsp sugar for 4 
servings). Break @ramen noodles{4.5%ounce} in half.

Open package of @diced skinless dark meat chicken{10%ounce} and drain off any 
excess liquid.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #large pan{} (medium pot for 4 servings) 
over medium-high heat. Add chicken in a single layer and cook, undisturbed, 
until just starting to brown, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in noodles and sauce mixture.

Increase heat to high. Cook, stirring constantly, until chicken is cooked 
through, noodles are tender, and sauce has thickened, ~{6-8%minutes}.

> While stirring, be sure to break up any noodles that are sticking together!

Remove pan from heat; add @red cabbage and carrot mix{4%ounce} and 
@bok choy and napa cabbage{4%ounce} to pan with chicken and noodles. Stir until 
veggies are slightly wilted and coated in sauce.

> If mixture seems too dry or noodles are too sticky, add splashes of water 
> until desired consistency is reached.

Taste and season with @?salt{} and @?pepper{} if desired.

Divide stir-fry between #shallow bowls{}. Top with @sesame seeds{1%tablespoon} 
and serve with @Sriracha{2%teaspoon} on the side.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.